WEBVTT

01:25.751 --> 01:27.887
[whooping]

01:27.920 --> 01:30.289
It's game time, shizznit!

01:30.322 --> 01:32.325
-Let's go!
-Now?

01:32.358 --> 01:34.294
Get your shoes on!

01:40.766 --> 01:42.368
-You still haven't told me--
-Shh!

01:42.401 --> 01:44.337
Matt, just tell me
where we're going.

01:44.370 --> 01:46.405
Will you just hurry up?

01:46.438 --> 01:49.309
It's like walking with
a fucking senior citizen.

02:09.728 --> 02:11.797
-Ms. Dillard's place?
-Yup.

02:11.830 --> 02:15.201
Matt, we can't go in there.
Are you crazy? There's fumes!

02:16.835 --> 02:19.305
-Where'd you get that?
-Army Navy Surplus.

02:19.338 --> 02:20.840
They only had one.

02:22.274 --> 02:23.776
-Well, how do you know it works?
-I don't.

02:23.809 --> 02:26.312
That's why you're going in
and I'm keeping watch.

02:26.345 --> 02:28.848
Matt, I'm not going
in that house!

02:28.881 --> 02:30.650
Ten grand.
Think about it.

02:30.683 --> 02:33.319
Think about what
it could do for Ma.

02:33.352 --> 02:37.390
-Why don't you go?
-I'm the oldest.
I made up the plan.

02:37.423 --> 02:39.292
I paid for the mask.
It's on you.

02:41.694 --> 02:43.663
But people take everything
when their homes get tented.

02:43.696 --> 02:45.898
Not when they're 82!

02:45.931 --> 02:48.701
Look, Tom Chowdee got community
service with old folks.

02:48.734 --> 02:50.470
He saw the cash.

02:51.737 --> 02:53.573
She's got Alzheimer's.

02:55.341 --> 02:58.277
Second floor bedroom,
wooden dresser, bottom drawer.

02:58.310 --> 03:00.279
In a candy tin.

03:00.312 --> 03:01.881
Well, I didn't know
there'd be fumes.

03:01.914 --> 03:04.350
You're not a fucking termite,
Joey, you'll be fine.

03:06.986 --> 03:09.289
Cut the tent.
Break a window.

03:18.897 --> 03:21.401
[glass shatters]

04:08.881 --> 04:10.850
Holy shit!

04:17.856 --> 04:20.593
-[panting]
-Give it!

04:24.897 --> 04:27.367
-Whoa.
-Anyone see us?

04:27.933 --> 04:29.068
No.

04:29.101 --> 04:30.469
No. Let's go before they do.

04:30.502 --> 04:32.038
Come on. Let's go!

04:32.071 --> 04:35.842
-I knew you had it in you.
-Sure you did.

04:40.346 --> 04:42.014
-Hey.
-Run. Run!

04:42.047 --> 04:44.550
Hey! You! No!

04:45.517 --> 04:47.987
Get back here! Hey!

04:48.020 --> 04:50.423
[guard] Come here!

04:51.690 --> 04:52.992
Stop!

05:02.801 --> 05:04.504
I can't keep up!

05:08.974 --> 05:11.077
-Oh!
-[thuds]

05:15.848 --> 05:17.383
[panting]

05:17.416 --> 05:19.385
[footsteps approach]

05:24.523 --> 05:25.891
-We lost him.
-No.

05:25.924 --> 05:29.429
[panting] No, he fell...
he fell in like a hole.

05:29.995 --> 05:31.831
I saw him.

05:31.864 --> 05:34.734
-[panting] You said they
didn't have security.
-They don't!

05:34.767 --> 05:36.969
-Then how--
-How do I know?

05:39.772 --> 05:41.974
-Did you say a hole?
-Yeah.

05:47.780 --> 05:49.749
I don't hear anyone
calling for help.

05:49.782 --> 05:51.751
I don't either.

05:52.885 --> 05:54.787
Oh, shit, I lost the gas mask.

05:56.755 --> 05:57.957
You owe me 30 bucks.

06:00.459 --> 06:01.694
What about the man?

06:01.727 --> 06:03.763
What do we do?

06:03.796 --> 06:05.665
Let's get home
and hide the cash.
We don't know what he saw.

06:29.021 --> 06:30.723
You eat too slow.

06:30.756 --> 06:33.393
-You eat too fast.
-Damn straight.

06:36.595 --> 06:39.465
-Use a napkin.
-I'll use your shirt
if I want to.

06:42.801 --> 06:44.570
-So what about--
-No. Don't.

06:46.071 --> 06:47.707
Not where Ma can hear.

06:50.709 --> 06:52.711
Hey, Ma, you can hear us, right?

06:52.744 --> 06:54.447
[woman] Matt? Joey?

06:54.480 --> 06:57.450
Can one of you boys
fetch me a diet soda?

07:08.594 --> 07:11.230
[newscaster on TV]
A developing situation, not
only in downtown Louisville.

07:11.263 --> 07:15.601
But we understand that usually
in the cases where there
is an officer shot,

07:15.634 --> 07:18.137
or there is a need to get
people to emergency care...

07:19.571 --> 07:20.673
Thanks, baby.

07:20.706 --> 07:23.075
[TV continues, indistinct]

07:23.108 --> 07:26.479
-You have a fun day?
-Um, I guess.

07:31.083 --> 07:33.686
Did you eat yet?

07:33.719 --> 07:36.122
-Uh, yeah. Mac and cheese.
-Mm.

07:39.725 --> 07:41.961
Okay, well...

07:41.994 --> 07:44.630
I'll cook you some shrimp
when I feel better.

07:45.197 --> 07:46.866
Maybe a steak.

07:51.203 --> 07:53.706
Oh, what a world.

07:53.739 --> 07:56.609
[newscaster] ...and Smith.
However, according
to court records,

07:56.642 --> 08:00.546
Smith filed a domestic violence
complaint against Gardner
in late May.

08:00.579 --> 08:03.082
On June 6th, the judge
granted an emergency
protection order...

08:16.094 --> 08:18.164
[counting indistinctly]

08:20.098 --> 08:22.935
The guy that was chasing us.
The guard?

08:22.968 --> 08:24.737
Yeah?

08:24.770 --> 08:27.006
I'm not sure he's okay.

08:27.039 --> 08:29.575
I'm pretty sure he, like,
fell in a well or something,
something deep.

08:29.608 --> 08:31.577
-So?
-So shouldn't
we go check on him?

08:31.610 --> 08:33.245
We can't go back there.

08:33.278 --> 08:35.948
When Ms. Dillard gets home,
she'll see she got robbed.

08:35.981 --> 08:37.683
She'll call the cops.

08:39.818 --> 08:42.755
Yeah, but what if he's hurt?

08:42.788 --> 08:44.156
Fuck that man.

08:44.189 --> 08:46.158
-Matt...
-No, come on, say it with me.

08:46.191 --> 08:48.127
Say "Fuck that man."
Count of three.

08:49.061 --> 08:51.964
One, two, three.

08:53.966 --> 08:55.234
Fuck that man.

08:56.335 --> 08:58.004
In your dreams.

10:08.940 --> 10:10.743
Hello?

10:14.713 --> 10:16.816
Anybody down there?

10:21.820 --> 10:22.855
Hello?

10:35.934 --> 10:37.370
Hello?

10:39.705 --> 10:41.373
[man] Hello?

10:41.406 --> 10:43.976
-Hey.
-Oh, thank God!

10:44.009 --> 10:46.812
I thought I
was trapped down here.

10:46.845 --> 10:51.316
I was chasing some kids
and then I fell.
I think I broke my ankle.

10:51.349 --> 10:54.453
You sound young.
I need to get some help.

10:54.486 --> 10:56.855
Can you... can you
tell your parents?

10:56.888 --> 11:00.125
My dad died last year
and my mom's real sick, so...

11:00.158 --> 11:03.229
-Do you have a cell phone?
-No. How far down are you?

11:04.229 --> 11:06.265
I don't know.
Like 20 feet.

11:06.298 --> 11:08.801
Something like that.
I can't climb out.

11:10.035 --> 11:11.470
Look, you don't have a phone?

11:11.503 --> 11:13.305
You already asked me that.

11:15.474 --> 11:18.377
-How old are you?
-I'll be 15 in three months.

11:18.410 --> 11:20.813
Okay. What's your name?

11:23.115 --> 11:24.250
Matt.

11:25.150 --> 11:27.152
Okay. Listen, Matt.

11:27.185 --> 11:29.488
I'm stuck down here,
I cannot get out by myself,

11:29.521 --> 11:31.790
and I'm gonna need you
to call 911.

11:31.823 --> 11:33.425
All right? If you can't do it,

11:33.458 --> 11:35.494
then just have your mom do it,
all right?

11:35.527 --> 11:37.362
What's your name?

11:37.395 --> 11:40.199
Hamby. H-A-M-B-Y.

11:40.232 --> 11:44.436
Uh, Dave Hamby, but everyone
just called me Hamby

11:44.469 --> 11:48.273
since high school
'cause there were three other
Daves in the class.

11:48.306 --> 11:52.878
But, listen,
you call 911, okay?

11:52.911 --> 11:55.013
Okay. I'll call. I mean,
I'll have my mom call.

11:55.046 --> 11:58.517
Okay. Good.
Good, that's great.

11:58.550 --> 12:00.285
Oh, that's good.
Thanks so much.

12:00.318 --> 12:03.522
This is scary stuff, you know?

12:03.555 --> 12:07.326
Yeah. Um, I'm gonna
get you some help, all right?

12:08.226 --> 12:09.461
Okay. Great.

12:09.494 --> 12:11.097
Great. Thank you.

12:12.097 --> 12:14.200
I'm not going anywhere.

12:21.006 --> 12:23.175
[video game sound effects]

12:26.077 --> 12:29.214
Matt. The guard,
he's still in that hole.

12:29.247 --> 12:31.283
-His name's Mr. Hamby.
-That's a dumb name.

12:31.316 --> 12:33.152
He's stuck
and he needs our help.

12:33.185 --> 12:34.453
Why? So he can arrest us?

12:35.954 --> 12:37.356
You didn't tell him
who you are?

12:37.389 --> 12:39.525
No. I didn't let him see me.

12:39.558 --> 12:42.861
-Fuck, I'm getting killed.
-Matt, we can't
just leave him there.

12:42.894 --> 12:44.330
Someone will hear him
if he yells loud enough.

12:46.264 --> 12:49.935
[sighs] But...

12:49.968 --> 12:52.104
-Oh, fuck!
-Wake up.

12:52.137 --> 12:53.505
What are you... [moans]

12:53.538 --> 12:57.342
We stole 12,600 bucks
from Ms. Dillard.

12:57.375 --> 12:59.178
Do you wanna get busted?

12:59.211 --> 13:01.580
[video game ends]

13:01.613 --> 13:03.883
Oh, son of a bitch, I'm dead.

13:07.853 --> 13:09.221
Hey.

13:10.021 --> 13:12.457
Hey. Don't cry.

13:12.490 --> 13:15.194
We pulled off
the perfect crime.

13:16.361 --> 13:18.564
If that guard sees you,
it's over.

13:22.133 --> 13:24.469
You're the one who went
in Ms. Dillard's house.
Not me.

13:24.502 --> 13:27.473
-Because you told me to!
-Well, you still did it.

13:28.273 --> 13:30.242
Robbery's a felony.

13:30.275 --> 13:32.244
They'll charge you
as a grown-up.

13:34.012 --> 13:35.347
You know what?

13:35.380 --> 13:37.583
If you don't help me
get him out of that hole,

13:37.616 --> 13:40.219
I'm gonna tell Mr. Hamby
exactly who we are!

13:44.322 --> 13:46.992
-Stop!
-No, you're not!

13:47.025 --> 13:49.495
We need that money
for Mom's medical bills.

13:51.663 --> 13:55.968
-Matt, stop!
-[Mother] Guys!
No fighting in the house!

13:56.935 --> 13:58.470
We're just playing around, Ma.

14:01.006 --> 14:02.875
You flinched.

14:06.444 --> 14:08.981
We can't leave him
to die, Matt!

14:10.282 --> 14:14.086
If... if you don't help me out,

14:14.119 --> 14:15.955
I'm gonna tell Ma everything.

14:19.691 --> 14:22.527
-You don't have the balls.
-Oh, yeah?

14:22.560 --> 14:25.430
You're the oldest, Matt.
She knows you push me around.

14:25.463 --> 14:26.899
You'll get in the most trouble.

14:29.634 --> 14:31.403
Fuck.

14:32.270 --> 14:33.639
You're such a girl.

14:34.506 --> 14:37.376
We need to help him.

14:37.409 --> 14:39.078
We could take him some water.

14:41.179 --> 14:42.314
Fine.

14:46.184 --> 14:47.620
We don't show our faces.

14:56.728 --> 14:58.697
You made this whole thing up,
didn't you?

14:58.730 --> 15:00.432
I'm telling you,
he was in the hole.

15:00.465 --> 15:02.100
Yeah? He better be,
â€˜cause if he's not...

15:02.133 --> 15:03.702
[Hamby groaning]

15:03.735 --> 15:07.172
-Oh, shit!
-See?

15:07.205 --> 15:09.942
-Hey. Mr. Hamby? It's me.
-[Hamby] Oh!

15:09.975 --> 15:12.278
Hey, you're back.
Did you bring the police?

15:13.511 --> 15:16.281
They're on their way.
My mom called them.

15:16.314 --> 15:17.549
I brought you some water.

15:20.118 --> 15:22.120
[Hamby] Ah! Ow!

15:22.153 --> 15:24.189
I'm sorry, I dropped it!
Why would you do that?

15:24.222 --> 15:27.559
It's okay!
Thanks. I got it.

15:27.592 --> 15:31.063
We checked on him.
He's fine. Let's go.

15:31.096 --> 15:33.966
He's not fine. He's still stuck.
We need to tell someone.

15:35.567 --> 15:37.336
Is someone up there with you?

15:37.369 --> 15:39.304
No. It's just me.

15:39.337 --> 15:42.274
Oh. Yeah. Come closer.

15:42.307 --> 15:45.510
-I want to see you.
-Yeah. Sure.

15:45.543 --> 15:47.746
What did you say your name
was again? Matt?

15:47.779 --> 15:51.516
-You told him my name?
-It just slipped out!

15:51.549 --> 15:53.652
I can hear you talking
to somebody up there.

15:53.685 --> 15:55.487
-No. I said I was alone.
-Yeah, but you're not.

15:55.520 --> 15:57.356
I can hear you.
It's another boy.

15:59.090 --> 16:01.360
[sighs]

16:01.393 --> 16:03.629
You're the two kids
I was chasing.

16:10.268 --> 16:12.304
Yeah, there's someone
else here all right.

16:15.040 --> 16:17.743
My name is David Hamby,
and I need your help.

16:20.378 --> 16:22.381
What are you two, brothers?

16:22.414 --> 16:24.082
[Matt] What's it to you?

16:24.115 --> 16:26.651
Look, I'm not gonna snitch.
Okay?

16:26.684 --> 16:28.487
I don't care what you guys
were up to.

16:28.520 --> 16:30.722
What do you think
we were up to?

16:30.755 --> 16:34.059
Playing tag? I don't know.
I'll say whatever you want.

16:36.327 --> 16:38.063
How do we know
you'll keep your word?

16:38.096 --> 16:40.232
Look, I was a kid once too,
all right?

16:40.265 --> 16:41.500
I know what it's like.

16:43.168 --> 16:45.670
Let me and my brother talk.

16:45.703 --> 16:48.607
Hey. We can save him.
We can do this.

16:48.640 --> 16:50.742
I bet he saw you sneaking
out of Ms. Dillard's house.

16:50.775 --> 16:53.345
Twenty years in jail.
Think about it.

16:53.378 --> 16:56.114
Let's tell Ma, okay?
This is too big for you and me.
She'll know what to do.

16:56.147 --> 16:57.649
We can't tell Ma we robbed
Ms. Dillard. Are you nuts?

16:57.682 --> 16:59.451
-[Hamby] Guys?
-Shut up!

16:59.484 --> 17:01.086
We're still talking.

17:01.119 --> 17:02.554
Let's just make
an anonymous phone call.

17:02.587 --> 17:04.689
There's a payphone
on Quigley at the 7-11.

17:04.722 --> 17:06.758
Mr. Hamby will sing like
Tweety Bird when he's safe.

17:06.791 --> 17:09.161
But, Matt, he knows our faces.

17:09.194 --> 17:11.596
It'll be worse if someone else
helps him and we don't.

17:11.629 --> 17:14.366
Maybe no one will help him.

17:14.399 --> 17:16.235
That could work too.

17:17.402 --> 17:19.204
Boys, come on, please!

17:19.237 --> 17:21.606
-I said shut up!
-I'm in a lot of pain!

17:21.639 --> 17:23.842
-Goddamn it! Shut up!
-Matt, don't yell at him.

17:23.875 --> 17:26.578
How hard is it to fetch
a grown-up, you stupid brats?

17:26.611 --> 17:29.281
-I'll show you
exactly how hard it is.
-Matt, stop!

17:34.285 --> 17:37.389
-Jesus, Matt!
-No! No! Ah!

17:37.422 --> 17:42.127
Goddamn it! Fuck you!

17:42.160 --> 17:44.163
I'm in charge now,
and I said shut up!

17:45.230 --> 17:46.598
Are you're crazy?
He'll hate us now.

17:46.631 --> 17:47.866
-He already hated us.
-No, he didn't.

17:47.899 --> 17:49.134
Why would you do that?

17:49.167 --> 17:51.503
Because it worked. Listen.

17:55.173 --> 17:57.643
Some people only
understand a harsh hand.

17:59.811 --> 18:01.346
It's like Dad always said.

18:04.182 --> 18:06.184
That man
is someone else's problem.

18:06.217 --> 18:08.387
Not mine, and not yours either.

18:12.557 --> 18:14.526
I'm sorry, Mr. Hamby!

18:41.553 --> 18:46.358
[TV plays indistinctly]

18:55.700 --> 18:58.336
[Mother]
It's cold outside, baby.

18:58.369 --> 19:02.574
-The TV says 43.
-Yeah.

19:02.607 --> 19:05.444
Can you fetch me a diet soda?

19:06.344 --> 19:07.679
Sure, Ma.

19:10.815 --> 19:13.719
What's wrong? Are we out?

19:15.587 --> 19:17.722
-No.
-Oh, good.

19:17.755 --> 19:20.492
Could you fetch me
a glass with some ice too?

19:20.525 --> 19:22.594
Yeah.

19:25.230 --> 19:28.266
-[TV continues indistinct]
-[sighs]

19:28.299 --> 19:29.668
What a world.

19:46.451 --> 19:48.187
Mr. Hamby?

19:48.920 --> 19:50.622
It's me. The nice one.

19:52.357 --> 19:55.360
My real name's Joey.
Matt's my brother.

19:57.395 --> 19:58.931
I brought you some food.

20:01.633 --> 20:04.469
Mr. Hamby. Are you asleep?

20:11.476 --> 20:13.879
Your brother
pissed on my face.

20:14.846 --> 20:17.482
Yeah, I know. Sorry.

20:19.984 --> 20:21.286
I brought you some food, though.

20:21.319 --> 20:23.855
I brought a bologna sandwich,

20:23.888 --> 20:26.992
uh, chips and a soda pop.

20:27.025 --> 20:28.594
Okay. Toss it down.

20:37.001 --> 20:39.238
Does your brother
know you're here?

20:41.039 --> 20:43.642
Yeah. I didn't think so.

20:50.014 --> 20:52.917
So, Joey, are you gonna help me?

20:52.950 --> 20:55.254
Seems like we
got a standoff here.

20:56.321 --> 20:58.823
Yeah. You know, um,

20:58.856 --> 21:00.725
my brother doesn't trust you.

21:00.758 --> 21:02.694
He thinks that you're
gonna get us in trouble.

21:02.727 --> 21:07.966
Well, you don't have to do
everything your brother says.

21:07.999 --> 21:10.402
-How old is he?
-Seventeen.

21:10.435 --> 21:12.737
-And you're what, 15?
-In three months.

21:12.770 --> 21:15.674
Well, you're old enough
to stand up to him.

21:20.545 --> 21:22.047
You seem like a good kid.

21:23.715 --> 21:26.318
You go to church, Joey?

21:26.351 --> 21:27.752
I mean,
I don't get there every Sunday.

21:27.785 --> 21:30.055
But you believe in God, right?

21:32.056 --> 21:35.927
-Yeah.
-Yeah, so do I.

21:35.960 --> 21:39.331
That's why you gotta
do the right thing.

21:39.364 --> 21:41.600
You gotta do
the Christian thing.

21:43.434 --> 21:46.071
Oh, God!

21:48.072 --> 21:50.875
Oh, my leg
hurts something awful.

21:50.908 --> 21:52.778
I can get you some
of my mom's painkillers.

21:54.011 --> 21:55.947
I can't stay down here forever.

21:56.881 --> 21:59.017
I know. I just...

21:59.050 --> 22:01.953
-I need some time to think.
-Think about what?

22:01.986 --> 22:05.724
No, you gotta take charge.
Gotta step up.

22:06.524 --> 22:08.360
I know. I should.

22:10.528 --> 22:14.333
Are you more afraid of your
brother than you are of God?

22:16.701 --> 22:18.870
I was afraid of my brother.

22:18.903 --> 22:21.773
He once kicked a basketball
in my face, broke my nose.

22:21.806 --> 22:23.608
That sounds like
something Matt would do.

22:23.641 --> 22:25.110
[chuckles]

22:25.143 --> 22:26.845
You have a sister?

22:26.878 --> 22:30.849
No. Just me and Matt. You?

22:30.882 --> 22:32.951
I had one.

22:33.918 --> 22:35.554
She died in a car wreck.

22:38.723 --> 22:41.626
-You love your mom, Joey?
-Of course.

22:42.593 --> 22:44.429
Yeah.

22:44.462 --> 22:46.031
I love my mom too.

22:47.765 --> 22:51.636
But, if you leave me
to die down here,

22:53.070 --> 22:54.706
how's she gonna feel?

22:54.739 --> 22:56.775
She'd be sad, I guess.

22:56.808 --> 22:58.377
Real sad.

23:00.711 --> 23:04.049
She'd be all alone,
except for my brother,

23:05.716 --> 23:08.453
and we've already determined
he's kind of an asshole.

23:08.486 --> 23:10.722
-[chuckles]
-[laughs]

23:11.856 --> 23:14.492
See, Joey? Help me out.

23:14.525 --> 23:17.962
Don't let the assholes win.

23:17.995 --> 23:21.166
I was so scared of you
at first, though.
When you were chasing us.

23:21.199 --> 23:24.002
I know, I was scared too.

