down a spell?" But...

44:26.262 --> 44:28.899
maybe you need to be left alone.

44:46.416 --> 44:48.385
Are you okay, baby?

44:49.986 --> 44:51.255
Yeah.

44:53.123 --> 44:58.028
-Matt's giving you grief again,
isn't he?
-No.

44:58.061 --> 45:00.197
He hasn't been the same
since Daddy died.

45:00.230 --> 45:03.233
Sure he has, Mom,
but it's just gotten worse.

45:06.803 --> 45:09.173
I don't have the strength
to deal with him.

45:10.440 --> 45:12.810
[sighs]
Not like a mother should.

45:13.810 --> 45:15.279
That's okay, Ma.

45:17.514 --> 45:20.117
You know,
as bad as your daddy was...

45:22.552 --> 45:25.355
some days I wish
he was still here.

45:40.870 --> 45:43.040
I'm sorry, Joey.

45:46.242 --> 45:48.345
I know, Ma.

45:51.080 --> 45:55.352
If you ever need to talk...

45:56.252 --> 45:57.954
here I am, okay.

45:57.987 --> 45:59.757
You know that, right?

46:00.356 --> 46:02.059
Yeah.

46:06.930 --> 46:08.799
Look.

46:10.233 --> 46:14.805
-A murderer's on the loose.
-A murderer?

46:14.838 --> 46:16.907
Yeah, they've been
showing his face all day.

46:16.940 --> 46:21.478
He shot his wife
and kids in Raleigh.

46:21.511 --> 46:23.346
He was spotted around here.

46:23.379 --> 46:26.316
"Armed and dangerous"
is what they say.

46:28.084 --> 46:30.086
He doesn't have
the jaw line of a killer,

46:30.119 --> 46:33.557
but you can never tell
until it's too late.

46:35.225 --> 46:38.428
His name
is Randy Michael Sadler.

46:38.461 --> 46:40.197
Holy shit!

46:40.230 --> 46:43.367
He shot his whole family.
Blew their brains out.

46:44.367 --> 46:47.204
I guess he just snapped,

46:47.237 --> 46:49.173
like people do.

46:50.607 --> 46:51.942
Baby?

46:52.909 --> 46:54.177
-Holy shit.
-Baby!

46:54.210 --> 46:56.213
I wasn't trying to scare you.

46:56.246 --> 46:58.281
I just want to keep you safe.

46:58.314 --> 47:02.352
Fuck! Holy fuck.
Holy fuck. Holy shit.

47:04.220 --> 47:05.889
Jesus!

47:05.922 --> 47:07.891
Jesus! Jesus!

47:07.924 --> 47:10.828
[static on walkie]

47:13.162 --> 47:15.833
[static on walkie]

47:17.533 --> 47:19.569
[Hamby] Joey.

47:19.602 --> 47:22.272
Joey. Are you there?

47:22.305 --> 47:24.875
Over.

47:37.086 --> 47:38.989
Mr. Hamby?

47:39.022 --> 47:43.126
[Hamby]
You forgot to say... "over."

47:45.995 --> 47:48.966
You're... you're alive?

47:49.565 --> 47:51.134
Over.

47:51.167 --> 47:53.370
[Hamby] Your brother...

47:53.403 --> 47:56.973
Was that... poison?

47:57.006 --> 47:59.643
From Ms. Dillard's
termite house.

48:00.510 --> 48:03.346
My lungs hurt...

48:03.379 --> 48:05.649
and my eyes aren't right.

48:05.682 --> 48:07.517
It's time.

48:07.550 --> 48:09.319
Get me out of here.

48:10.353 --> 48:12.222
No more excuses.

48:13.256 --> 48:17.561
-Mr. Hamby?
-Yeah?

48:19.395 --> 48:21.298
I know who you really are.

48:26.569 --> 48:28.105
Joey...

48:29.472 --> 48:31.375
Come see me in the morning.

49:04.774 --> 49:06.510
How come you're still alive?

49:12.715 --> 49:15.552
You dropped this
when I was chasing you.

49:20.256 --> 49:22.058
You saved my life.

49:22.091 --> 49:24.761
Why were you chasing us?
You're gonna hurt us?

49:24.794 --> 49:27.230
I saw you robbing the place.

49:27.263 --> 49:29.333
I was gonna take what you stole.

49:31.267 --> 49:33.403
Things didn't
go according to plan.

49:33.436 --> 49:36.306
So I guess I should call you
Randy from now on.

49:38.574 --> 49:40.110
Hey, Joey.

49:42.445 --> 49:44.414
How did your dad die?

49:45.248 --> 49:46.449
I never asked you.

49:46.482 --> 49:49.486
-He got shot.
-Shot?

49:52.288 --> 49:55.125
He was drunk and, um,

49:55.158 --> 49:58.294
messed with the wrong person.

49:58.327 --> 50:01.498
He had cancer anyway.
Lung cancer. [sniffs]

50:01.531 --> 50:03.200
My mom got it too.

50:04.567 --> 50:07.237
Tough draw.

50:07.270 --> 50:09.639
Both my folks died
in a car wreck.

50:09.672 --> 50:11.208
Just like your sister?

50:13.476 --> 50:15.112
Yeah.

50:16.679 --> 50:18.181
Just like her, Joey.

50:18.214 --> 50:20.150
You never even
had a sister, did you?

50:25.321 --> 50:26.723
Why didn't you ever
tell me your real name?

50:26.756 --> 50:29.126
Same reason you
didn't tell me yours.

50:30.793 --> 50:32.596
So is it true?

50:35.364 --> 50:37.501
You know, what they said
about you in the news?

50:39.469 --> 50:42.672
Well, it probably went down

50:42.705 --> 50:44.641
a little different
than they said it did.

50:44.674 --> 50:48.144
Why'd you want me to call
the cops? There's a manhunt.

50:48.177 --> 50:50.047
Well, maybe I had a plan.

50:52.448 --> 50:55.185
They said that you...
you killed your family.

50:56.486 --> 51:00.223
Your wife and your two kids,
eight and ten.

51:00.256 --> 51:02.659
Then you burned your house down.

51:02.692 --> 51:04.794
What do you think
about that, Joey?

51:04.827 --> 51:06.563
[Joey] Why were you wearing
a security guard outfit?

51:06.596 --> 51:10.366
They say you work
at a tire factory.

51:10.399 --> 51:12.836
[chuckles]
How about that?

51:12.869 --> 51:14.671
A tire factory.

51:14.704 --> 51:17.274
Why can't you just
give me a straight answer?

51:19.308 --> 51:22.846
Maybe I ran into a security
guard and stole his clothes.

51:24.147 --> 51:26.516
Desperate men
do desperate things.

51:27.750 --> 51:30.487
So do you still want me
to call the cops?

51:30.520 --> 51:32.322
Oh...

51:32.355 --> 51:35.625
It's a bit more challenging
now that I'm all over the news.

51:37.360 --> 51:39.596
But if you were to get a rope,

51:39.629 --> 51:42.432
I wouldn't say no.

51:42.465 --> 51:45.168
Tie it to a tree.
I could climb out.

51:46.469 --> 51:47.704
You know, I could turn you in.

51:47.737 --> 51:49.306
I bet there's big reward money.

51:50.540 --> 51:52.375
I bet there is.

51:53.776 --> 51:56.279
But you're not gonna do that,
are you, Joey?

52:02.652 --> 52:04.254
[groans]

52:06.722 --> 52:08.425
Now, go get that rope.

52:09.692 --> 52:12.228
There's a rope in the garage.
I can get it.

52:12.261 --> 52:13.863
Good man.

52:13.896 --> 52:17.600
Bring it here quick.
We're running out of time.

52:17.633 --> 52:19.236
First I got a question.

52:20.236 --> 52:22.405
Actually, it's more of a...

52:22.438 --> 52:23.773
a favor than a question.

52:23.806 --> 52:26.709
-Hit me.
-If I get you that rope

52:26.742 --> 52:29.179
and help you out...

52:32.815 --> 52:35.318
will you come back to the house
and punish Matt for me?

52:37.453 --> 52:39.623
-Joey?
-Yes, Randy?

52:41.357 --> 52:43.260
It would be my delight.

52:48.631 --> 52:51.634
[indistinct shouting]

52:51.667 --> 52:54.771
All you do pop pills
and watch TV all day!

52:54.804 --> 52:57.407
Don't you rag my ass
about how I live!

52:57.440 --> 52:59.576
[sobbing]
I'm worried about you!

52:59.609 --> 53:02.378
The manager of Red Carper Inn
called and said...

53:02.411 --> 53:04.314
Screw that guy, he's lying!

53:04.347 --> 53:06.516
-...you and Tom Chowdee...
-I've never been in that dump!

53:06.549 --> 53:08.552
-...threw a party
and wrecked a room.
-Hey, Matt!

53:09.452 --> 53:10.987
Mom!

53:11.020 --> 53:13.856
[Mother] Go up to your room.
Lock the door.

53:13.889 --> 53:15.858
Stop talking about me
like I'm not even in here!

53:15.891 --> 53:17.860
He's been stealing
my pain pills too.

53:17.893 --> 53:20.630
-No, you're fuckin' lying!
-Matt, stop!

53:20.663 --> 53:22.832
-Not my TV!
-Matt, Matt, Matt!

53:22.865 --> 53:26.669
Okay, I was taking
your pain pills. That was me,
I was taking them.

53:26.702 --> 53:28.738
-What? You?
-That was me.

53:30.273 --> 53:32.542
You? Why?

53:32.575 --> 53:35.278
-I... I was bored.
-Why?

53:35.311 --> 53:37.314
-Time for rehab.
-Shut up!

53:39.715 --> 53:42.586
[sobbing] I feel so helpless
with you boys.

53:43.419 --> 53:45.688
[sobbing] Baby, can...

53:45.721 --> 53:48.558
-Can you get me a diet soda?
-Sure, Ma.

53:51.560 --> 53:53.396
You two make me sick.

53:54.297 --> 53:56.633
Baby. Ma! Baby. Ma!

53:57.767 --> 54:00.403
-Fuck it.
-[clattering]

54:00.436 --> 54:02.239
I hate this place.

54:04.507 --> 54:06.843
I'll get you that soda, Ma.

54:06.876 --> 54:09.412
I'm helping you clean up, okay?

54:34.036 --> 54:38.375
-Here, baby. [groans]
-It's okay, Ma.

55:22.518 --> 55:24.787
-[Randy] That you, Joey?
-Yeah, I got the rope.

55:24.820 --> 55:27.557
Okay. Good man.

55:27.590 --> 55:28.991
[Joey] Yeah,
this might take a while.

55:29.024 --> 55:32.562
That's okay.
Take your time and do it right.

55:33.496 --> 55:35.431
Tie it around the nearest tree.

55:35.464 --> 55:37.700
Do you know how
to make a clove hitch?

55:37.733 --> 55:40.937
-My dad taught me.
-All right.
Make sure it's tight.

55:40.970 --> 55:43.773
It's got to support
all of my weight.

55:43.806 --> 55:46.009
-Oh, it'll hold.
-Okay.

55:55.651 --> 55:59.589
-Okay, here it comes.
-All right. There we go.

55:59.622 --> 56:03.360
Good. Come on. Little further.

56:04.727 --> 56:05.895
Got it!

56:08.431 --> 56:10.100
All right, Joey, stand back.

56:12.101 --> 56:15.505
[grunting]

56:23.579 --> 56:27.083
[panting, grunting]

56:27.116 --> 56:29.386
Pull me up. Pull me up.

56:34.690 --> 56:37.827
[moans, sighs]

56:38.994 --> 56:40.563
Oh, wow.

56:44.033 --> 56:47.837
Get me a branch for a cane.

56:47.870 --> 56:51.007
-Otherwise I'm no good
for walking.
-Okay.

56:51.040 --> 56:53.877
[sighs, pants]

56:56.078 --> 56:58.148
I forgot what freedom was.

57:04.086 --> 57:06.689
[groans]

57:11.193 --> 57:13.596
Okay. Help me up.

57:14.730 --> 57:16.599
[moans] Okay.

57:19.835 --> 57:22.071
-You okay?
-Yeah.

57:23.873 --> 57:24.874
Ow!

57:27.676 --> 57:30.180
[sighs, pants]

57:32.081 --> 57:34.784
-Sorry about this, Joey.
-Sorry about what?

57:39.622 --> 57:41.458
[panting]

57:42.858 --> 57:46.596
Randy? Have you had that gun
in the hole the entire time?

57:46.629 --> 57:48.898
It didn't do me
much good in the hole.

57:50.065 --> 57:51.935
Different story outside.

57:53.969 --> 57:57.006
Are... are you gonna shoot me?

58:02.011 --> 58:03.213
Nah.

58:08.617 --> 58:10.820
Here. [sniffs]

58:10.853 --> 58:11.988
You take it.

58:12.021 --> 58:13.723
I don't want it.
I don't want it.

58:13.756 --> 58:15.492
You might like the feel.

58:18.193 --> 58:20.863
I wish I had two.

58:20.896 --> 58:22.665
I'd take you hunting.

58:23.165 --> 58:24.834
Teach you.

58:25.701 --> 58:27.203
Like your daddy wanted.

58:29.738 --> 58:31.107
Go on, then.

58:32.775 --> 58:36.779
-Is it loaded?
-It's loaded. Safety's off.

58:37.947 --> 58:39.949
You could shoot a man.

58:40.950 --> 58:43.553
[imitates gunshots]

58:47.122 --> 58:49.893
-[imitates gunshots]
-Looks good on you.

59:00.736 --> 59:02.872
Police are looking for you
in five states.

59:04.773 --> 59:06.543
Five states, huh?

59:07.076 --> 59:08.778
That's big.

59:08.811 --> 59:10.947
You shot your family
and that's all you can say?

59:12.681 --> 59:14.784
Sometimes...

59:17.052 --> 59:19.221
That doesn't matter now.

59:19.254 --> 59:20.857
It matters to me.

59:25.060 --> 59:26.996
You better give me
that gun back.

59:40.275 --> 59:42.111
Tell me what you
were going to say.

59:44.279 --> 59:46.316
Sometimes...

59:49.018 --> 59:51.921
you wish you could
go back in time.

59:53.789 --> 59:55.925
Before life knocked
your knees out.

59:59.194 --> 1:00:03.366
-I should shoot you right now.
-Probably so.

1:00:14.176 --> 1:00:15.378
Take your gun.

1:00:19.815 --> 1:00:22.251
Take me to your house.

1:00:22.284 --> 1:00:24.654
I'm gonna need cash and a car.

1:00:26.188 --> 1:00:28.224
And we'll settle
that score with your brother.

1:00:28.257 --> 1:00:31.127
Right.

1:00:31.160 --> 1:00:34.430
Let's just scare him, though,
all right? Don't hurt him.

1:00:34.463 --> 1:00:36.098
Exactly.

1:00:36.131 --> 1:00:39.369
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

1:00:57.286 --> 1:01:00.756
Just let me do
the talking, all right?
She saw you on the news.

1:01:00.789 --> 1:01:02.659
Fair enough.

1:01:04.226 --> 1:01:07.096
-Hey, Ma.
-Baby.

1:01:07.129 --> 1:01:09.966
-Can you fetch me a diet soda?
-Not today.

1:01:20.909 --> 1:01:22.244
You're...

1:01:22.277 --> 1:01:25.247
you're Randy Michael Sadler.

1:01:25.280 --> 1:01:27.984
-From the TV!
-Don't worry.

1:01:28.917 --> 1:01:31.087
I'm not gonna hurt you.

1:01:31.120 --> 1:01:33.156
Go sit on the couch by your mom.

1:01:35.357 --> 1:01:38.494
-Baby...
-It's okay, Ma. It's okay.

1:01:38.527 --> 1:01:40.429
He's not gonna hurt us.

1:01:40.462 --> 1:01:43.332
-Is Matt home?
-Oh, no, no.

1:01:43.365 --> 1:01:45.068
He's... he's out.

1:01:51.540 --> 1:01:53.776
You take whatever you need
and you get out.

1:01:53.809 --> 1:01:56.178
Just don't hurt my boy.

1:01:56.211 --> 1:01:58.114
Your boys have some money.

1:01:58.147 --> 1:02:00.249
And Joey said there's
a car I can use?

1:02:01.850 --> 1:02:04.353
In the... in the garage.

1:02:05.420 --> 1:02:07.289
Their daddy's old truck.

1:02:07.322 --> 1:02:10.793
All right.
I'll get out of your hair soon.

1:02:10.826 --> 1:02:13.229
-I'm sorry about this, ma'am.
-You should be.

1:02:13.262 --> 1:02:16.799
-Your mom have a cell phone?
-No.

1:02:18.500 --> 1:02:21.337
Grab that phone so
she doesn't call the cops.

1:02:22.504 --> 1:02:24.941
Get me some fresh clothes
and a towel.

1:02:25.808 --> 1:02:27.543
Meet me by the car.

1:02:27.576 --> 1:02:30.179
-Sure, Randy.
-You're on his side?

1:02:31.980 --> 1:02:34.150
-It's complicated.
-Baby!

1:02:34.183 --> 1:02:36.419
Just don't move
'cause he might shoot you.

1:02:38.020 --> 1:02:39.522
Also, you still want
that diet soda?

1:02:39.555 --> 1:02:41.491
Not right now.

1:02:42.057 --> 1:02:43.926
Okay.

1:02:46.128 --> 1:02:48.498
Excuse me,
Officer Friendly?

1:02:50.199 --> 1:02:53.469
-You lost, son?
-No such luck.

1:02:53.502 --> 1:02:57.373
-Well, we're working here.
-I need to talk to you
about Ms. Dillard's place.

1:02:58.841 --> 1:03:00.476
You know something
about that broken window?

1:03:00.509 --> 1:03:02.111
I sure do.

1:03:02.144 --> 1:03:03.579
And it's more
than just a broken window.

1:03:03.612 --> 1:03:05.915
Yeah? Hey, Crane.

1:03:08.050 --> 1:03:09.451
What's going on?

1:03:09.484 --> 1:03:11.554
I saw this kid the other day
sneak into this house,

1:03:11.587 --> 1:03:13.455
right through the termite tent.

1:03:13.488 --> 1:03:16.425
Came out with cash
in both his hands. Boats full.

1:03:16.458 --> 1:03:18.795
What kid?
You know his name?

1:03:20.095 --> 1:03:21.864
His name's Joey.

1:03:23.165 --> 1:03:25.368
He lives in my house. He's...

1:03:27.169 --> 1:03:28.470
Well, he's my little brother.

1:03:28.503 --> 1:03:30.940
-He's your little brother?
-Yes, sir.

1:03:30.973 --> 1:03:33.409
I saw what he stole,
and it was a whole lot.

1:03:35.878 --> 1:03:37.413
I can take you
to the cash if you want.

1:03:37.446 --> 1:03:39.115
You can see for yourself.

1:03:45.487 --> 1:03:48.190
It's really never been driven
since your daddy was shot?

1:03:48.223 --> 1:03:50.893
My ma's got a car,
but Matt never learned how.

1:03:50.926 --> 1:03:53.563
Huh. Well,
I'll tell you one thing.

1:03:54.630 --> 1:03:57.133
Your dad sure
loved this truck.

1:04:00.035 --> 1:04:03.039
-He ever take you riding in it?
-Yeah, sometimes.

1:04:07.109 --> 1:04:09.212
-Randy?
-Yep.

1:04:13.649 --> 1:04:16.352
Can you...
can you take me with you?

1:04:17.653 --> 1:04:19.589
Wherever you're going?

1:04:21.423 --> 1:04:25.027
Yeah. I knew you were
gonna ask me that.

1:04:28.063 --> 1:04:30.199
I'm not planning
on ever coming back here.

1:04:30.232 --> 1:04:32.534
And besides,

1:04:32.567 --> 1:04:35.238
I don't think your mama
would approve.

1:04:36.972 --> 1:04:39.275
Oh, sure she would.

1:04:39.308 --> 1:04:41.610
So I'm the Pied Piper now? Huh?

1:04:41.643 --> 1:04:43.279
[chuckles]

1:04:46.348 --> 1:04:48.284
If you don't take me with you,

1:04:48.317 --> 1:04:50.386
I'll tell the police
everything I know about you.

1:04:50.419 --> 1:04:53.088
Everything.

1:04:53.121 --> 1:04:55.491
Blackmail, huh?
Say it ain't so, Joe.

1:04:55.524 --> 1:04:58.628
-I'm not bluffing!
-[chuckles] I know.

1:05:03.598 --> 1:05:06.035
Why don't you come on
and take a ride with me?

1:05:07.436 --> 1:05:10.172
-[bangs on truck]
-What about Matt? You promised.

1:05:10.205 --> 1:05:14.010
Yeah. We'll find him
along the way. Come on.

1:05:16.411 --> 1:05:18.047
Just up here.

1:05:18.080 --> 1:05:19.916
It's the little
white house on the corner.

1:05:22.617 --> 1:05:24.353
Oh, shit, that's my dad's truck.

1:05:25.988 --> 1:05:28.123
Hey, wait, wait.
Matt's in that cop car.

1:05:28.156 --> 1:05:30.226
Matt's in the back
of that cop car.

1:05:32.027 --> 1:05:34.563
What do we do?
What do we do?

1:05:37.299 --> 1:05:39.936
[laughs]

1:05:41.703 --> 1:05:45.041
Uh... you got me.

1:05:49.611 --> 1:05:51.614
-We're gonna be all right, Joey.
-How?

1:05:56.218 --> 1:06:00.222
Just put your fingers in your
ears when the shooting starts.

1:06:00.255 --> 1:06:03.592
The shooting? The cops might
not know who you are, Randy!

1:06:03.625 --> 1:06:07.029
-Wait, wait, wait. You, you--
-Stay in the car.

1:06:07.062 --> 1:06:09.098
Fingers in your ears.

1:06:15.504 --> 1:06:18.040
-Shit. It's Mr. Hamby
from the hole.
-[Crane] The hole?

1:06:18.073 --> 1:06:20.042
This kid don't
make a lick of sense.

1:06:20.075 --> 1:06:23.179
-No, you don't understand.
-I gotta check it out.

1:06:25.213 --> 1:06:27.583
-How you doing, officer?
-Fucking car. Fuck!

1:06:27.616 --> 1:06:30.085
-Let me out of this
fuckin' car right now!
-[Crane] Calm down!

1:06:30.118 --> 1:06:32.087
-What is wrong with you?
-Can I help you with something?

1:06:32.120 --> 1:06:33.655
If you don't mind, I'd like to
ask you a couple of questions.

1:06:33.688 --> 1:06:36.025
-Oh, yeah.
-I have a guy in the back...

1:06:36.058 --> 1:06:37.326
No! Gun!

1:06:41.730 --> 1:06:43.299
Let me out of this fuckin' car!

1:06:46.068 --> 1:06:47.770
We don't have to do this!

1:06:47.803 --> 1:06:49.572
There's kids around!

1:06:51.506 --> 1:06:53.442
-I recognize you!
-I figured you would.

1:06:53.475 --> 1:06:55.478
Put down the gun!
I gotta take you in!

1:07:00.215 --> 1:07:01.517
Get off the street!

1:07:03.752 --> 1:07:05.454
Randy, you shot that cop.

1:07:05.487 --> 1:07:09.258
He'll be okay.
He just got to get doctored up.

1:07:11.326 --> 1:07:13.829
-That's my brother in your car!
-I said get back inside!

1:07:13.862 --> 1:07:16.832
You heard the lady.
That's good advice.

1:07:16.865 --> 1:07:19.502
[Crane] Put down the gun
or I'll shoot!

1:07:22.404 --> 1:07:25.207
-Jesus Christ, move!
-Hey, hey, hey! Wait!

1:07:25.240 --> 1:07:27.776
You're not gonna take Randy.
All right?
You're not gonna hurt him!

1:07:27.809 --> 1:07:29.645
-Get out of the--
-[gunshot]

1:07:36.651 --> 1:07:37.686
Stay down!

1:07:40.455 --> 1:07:42.358
I'm not worth it.

1:07:42.858 --> 1:07:44.660
Promise.

1:07:53.702 --> 1:07:55.371
